2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes algorithms for waking up a network with multiple channels, which involves distributed computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes deterministic and randomized algorithms for waking up the network, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of waking up a network with multiple channels, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and transmission rates. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes algorithms for waking up a network, which can be seen as a control problem in systems and control.
